title: Prime Minister of Ukraine - Wikipedia
snippet: Two prime ministers were born in the Russian SFSR. The current prime minister is Yulia Svyrydenko, who was confirmed by the Verkhovna Rada on 17 July 2025. She replaced Denys Shmyhal, who had been sworn in on 4 March 2020 following the resignation of Oleksiy Honcharuk.

title: Yulia Svyrydenko - Wikipedia
snippet: Yulia Anatoliivna Svyrydenko (Ukrainian: Юлія Анатоліївна Свириденко, IPA: [ˈjul⁽ʲ⁾ijɐ ɐnɐˈtɔl⁽ʲ⁾ijiu̯nɐ swɪrɪˈdɛnko]; born 25 December 1985) is a Ukrainian politician who has served as the 19th prime minister of Ukraine since 17 July 2025.

title: List of prime ministers of Ukraine - Wikipedia
